<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by BCS, The Chartered Institute for IT_x0002_ (WSC084)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">BCS, The Chartered Institute for IT</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (WSC084)</span></p><h1 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Executive Summary</span></h1><h1 style="margin:0pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">This submission </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">focuses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> on women in IT jobs. Current </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">funding for women in STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">appears to be biased towards academia and engineering</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and we therefore</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> present an industry view of issues, evidence, best practice and recommendations for women in IT.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span></h1><h1 style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 27pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"></span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Only 15% of employees are women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> numbers are falling</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">;</span></h1><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Fewer than 10% of managers are women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The pay gap is 22%</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">70% of women with STEM degrees do not use them in their career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 19.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Contributory causes are culture, image of women in the media, lack of role models, recruitment and retention policies, limited career </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">policies and little flexible working</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">There is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">a wealth of research demonstrating the value of diversity to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> businesses, especially increasing the number of women operating on boards.  However, progress increasing the participation of women (particularly in IT) is slow.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our recommendations cover:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">pening and consulting on the debat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> about q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uotas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Reusing </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">current r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">esources</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">not reinventing the wheel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Providing appropriate role models through TV and the media</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Secur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">unding </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for the medium to long term </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">across </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">political </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">administrations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Improv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and monitor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ecruitment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">processes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Audit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the gender pay g</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ap</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Publish</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> best practice about career and r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">etention</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Sign</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> industry up to the programme, provid</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> incentives and monitor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> results</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">The Problem</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> know</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that women choose IT as a profession less often than men</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and that women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">leave the profession for other careers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. We would like to see this change, as there are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">exceptionally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> good opportunities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> flourish in IT environments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BCS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">believe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that the UK IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ector would be strengthened by innovation and pr</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ofit benefits which diversity in the workplace brings.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Today’s job market is very competitive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> IT is both the enabler of savings and the engine of growth, and people with skills and experience in IT are likely to be more in demand than people with other s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">kill sets</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> IT is integral to every business process, and IT teams interact with business teams, working together in exciting and dynamic environments to transform companies. Careers in IT can be varied, stimulating</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> flexible</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">However, it seems that fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r many women IT isn’t regarded as a great place to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">work</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  WISE, formerly the UKRC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> for Women in SET</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">has published the following</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Only 13% of all STEM jobs in the UK are occupied by women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women make up only 15% of ICT professionals and 21% of those IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Service Delivery positions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Just over one in 10 of STEM business owners are women compared to 1:3 in non-STEM businesses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Fewer than one in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">10</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> STEM managers are female</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Males dominated the number of undergraduate degrees in Computer Science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Whilst girls make up 44% of GCSE and 39% of A Level entries, they make up </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">79% and 69% of the A* to C grades achieved in June 2012, proving that females do not lack aptitude and ability in the subject. Indeed, historically, women have received the greater p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ercentage of the highest grades</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Females obtained 20% of ICT higher education degrees in 2011/12</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Men are 6 times more likely to work in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">than women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 10.06pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The pay gap </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is 22% through a combination of high flying males commanding large salaries and few </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women at this level; and a true gap (11%) in salaries. There were no reductions in the pay gap in science and technology between 2003 and 2008</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">The Value of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">ndustry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold"> to the UK </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">conomy</span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The IT industry directly contributes 8% (£75 billion) to the U</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">K’s total GVA</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The scope of the value of IT to the UK economy transcends the IT sector alone, with around 40% of the IT workforce employed in other industries</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">benefiting business through increased efficiency provided by new technology. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he McKinsey </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Reports; Women Matter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (2007)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and Women Matter 2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(2010)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, outline the benefits in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">RO</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">profit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and share-price</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> when boards and senior management teams include diverse members.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ork by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Cedric Herring, University of Illinois, in a paper</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">titled</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Does Diversit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">y Pay? Race, Gender, and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">the Business Case for Diversity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">examines the impact of racial and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">gender diversity on business performance</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. He makes a business case for diversity</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> arguing that a diverse workforce produce</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> better results and offers a direct ROI.  His research, as with that of McKinsey</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> promises larger profit and greater earnings.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Additionally</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the law firm Reed Smith launched a report in partnership with Winmark showing how global companies could get the be</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">st ROI from gender diversity. The "</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Gender Balancing: It's Good Business</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">" report</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">surveyed a range of FTSE100, FTSE250 and leading firms to determine UK businesses’ level of commitment to gender diversity and practical initiatives.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The report</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> found</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, as with the others cited here, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">that</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> overall business effectiveness and profit </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">was</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> enhanced when women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">were</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> included in every level of enterprise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We have consulted with a number of industry stakeholders who all testify to the value of diversity in the i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ndustry:</span></p><p style="margin:5pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Creating a diverse workforce at Thomson Reuters is a critical component of our vision and advances the focus on collaboration and innovation by bringing more women onto our technology teams. We are currently working on a program that we are callin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">g, “from college to career”, which will build bridges from colleges to active careers at Thomson Reuters. Part of this initiative is the commitment to recruit and develop future female technology leaders. By creating more diverse teams we add another innov</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ation dimension advancing future solutions and adding new perspectives and ideas.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Jane Moran, CIO, Thomson Reuters</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">The leak of women into STEM starts in school and we see girls are not encouraged or properly advised of the richness of a career in IT, and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">the industry needs a style makeover to move on from the “geeky” back office image it still has. We tend to describe our roles in a very technical way expecting use of “cyber security” will be a major draw – and it is a turn off instead. The use of gaming, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">fun technology and more retail linked brands is much more </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">helpful. Google, Amazon and e-bay don’t have the same problems the more traditional B to B service companies experience in attracting girls.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Ann Brown, Senior Vice President HR, Capgemini UK</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">There </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">aren’t any simple problems or challenges left.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> Almost everything we do is beyond the capacity and capabilities of the individual.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> We depend entirely on the expanse of talent we can muster by bringing teams together, and like it or not, there are some thi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ngs that men and women do equally well, and there are a set of things that one does better than the other.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> If you don’t build teams with a balance of men and women, you’re building teams with unnecessary limitations.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">In Visa Europe we try and create these</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> balanced teams.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> Starting in our Visa Apprentice programme and lasting as long as necessary, we provide accelerated development and support programmes and specifically for or female members of staff, to try and accelerate the slow but inevitable rebalanci</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ng of men and women in all roles in business and technology. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Steve Chambers, CIO, VISA</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Women are an integral and important part of our Global IT team at BG Group. BG Group believes that we will deliver better and more sustainable results if we have a cul</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">ture where different perspectives are encouraged and considered. To achieve this, we aim to build a workforce that is diverse – in ethnicity, gender, background and approach.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Angus McCallum, CIO, BG Group</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Women are leading key areas of our business from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">central technology services to strategy to content and are instrumental in our progress as an organisation. We believe that businesses which better reflect society, in all its diversity, will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">be more successful in the long-term.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Selwyn Castleden, IS Direct</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">or Sky</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Network Services, BskyB</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Creating an inclusive workplace is something that IBM has always set out to achieve. Diverse teams energise and challenge each other to deliver strong business results and innovative ideas which is why IBM in the UK and Irel</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">and continues to employee people from all lifestyles and backgrounds. It makes perfect business sense and is essential to the way we work and the way we operate our business.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">David Stokes, IBM UK and Ireland General Manager</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">At Deloitte our business thrive</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">s on the many and varied talents of our people. The ability to attract, retain and advance talented women is an important part of this. We have set objectives to improve the representation of women in senior roles to ensure women have every opportunity to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">develop and progress. We recognise and highly value the qualities female leaders can bring to the business and are working within firm and the wider market to foster these strengths.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Rebecca George OBE, Partner Public Sector Health, Deloitte LLP</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">auses</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">bsence of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">omen in IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> and Best Practice </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> shows several themes which inhibit girls and younger women to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">pursue</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> careers in the IT industry and cause them to migrate away from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">technology </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">roles</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Cultures in</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ector </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">orkforce</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2005 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">study conducted for Intellect and the DTI concluded that women were leaving the industry because they felt undervalued, found their management unsupportive, did not feel included in the male dominated industry, and felt the long hours culture</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> was </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">un</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">comfortable for them</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.2 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women act differently from men in the workplace. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women sell themselves differently in interviews and performance appraisals.  In predominantly male environments, if men are not aware of these differences, women miss out </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">on networking, mentoring and promotion opportunities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Everywoman (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">www.everywoman.com</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">) is an excellent example of an organisation providing advice, networking resources and connections to help women address the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">issues often faced by women in traditionally male dominated environments</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">any women report that the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">re is an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> 'old boys</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> network' </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">culture </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">creat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">impenetrable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> glass ceiling</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> One recent statistic states that 58% of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">US </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">male CEOs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in the 500 largest compa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are over </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t tall, whilst only 14% of the population are over that height</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">suggest</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> deep rooted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">bias in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">selection</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of top executives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">words and phrases</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">crop up in research and interviews, including </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">glass ceiling, glass cliff, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">macho/aggressive and bullying culture, lack of recognition, having to work extra hard to prove themselves, long hours culture, old-boys club.  If these</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> reflect</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">industry </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">norms </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">impact the retention of women, they need to be addressed in order </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">stem t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he decline in women in the industry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.1.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> will be discriminated against even when the employer has policies which aim to do the right thing</span><a name="_ftnref6"></a><a href="#_ftn6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  Gender Schemas</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, also known as </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nconscious </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ias</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">socialised into the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">populace from birth, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">define the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">assumptions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> by which individuals are judged.  This is particularly important when recruitment, promotion and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">performance </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">assessment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">decisions are made</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Image of Women in IT in the Media </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Government has invested in research into the roles that TV and the media play </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in gender stereotyping</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> effect on STEM career decisions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘Media coverage of science, particularly television programmes, is a key </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">place</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">where young peoples’ perc</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">eptions of STEM and its relationship with society are formed…the images young people see presented on television are generally thought to have some influence on the choices some students </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">make about their future careers;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’</span><a name="_ftnref7"></a><a href="#_ftn7">[7]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In the UK</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the numbers of women opting </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> IT studies at university continues to fall</span><a name="_ftnref8"></a><a href="#_ftn8">[8]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e believe that without adequate positive representation in the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">edia young women will not choose careers in our industry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> despite the good work done by earlier programmes such </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as Computer Clubs for Girls</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (CC4G)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.2.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A relatively recent example of the power of media representations is the upswing in the take-up of Forensic Science courses by young women (women now represent two thirds</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK students on Forensic Science courses)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  This has been largely attributed to the portrayal of a female forensic pathologist in the BBC TV production </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Silent Witness</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of Role Models </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The lack of visible role models allow</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> gender and industry stereotypes to persist, to reinforce the ‘nerdy’ image of the IT or technical professional</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. That these perceptions persist sustains the lack of attraction of the IT sector for young </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">females</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. It is simply not a career default choice. S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">chools and HEIs find it difficult to challenge the stereotypes and offer girls an image of an exciting career in IT and technology.  Equally, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">if </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women already embarked on IT careers cannot see equality of opportunity and subsequent equality of reward in fe</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">male role models, they will opt for other industries where opportunities for advancement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are visible.</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Many organisations have built education outreach programmes, selecting and training women to go into schools to present on the benefits of women in IT. BC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">S has been involved with a programme started by Deloitte and Atos and we are aware of other industry based schemes w</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ith</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> the same motivations.  However, these schemes are voluntary, not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">incentivised</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or rewarded, and funding is usually time bounded</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Other </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Ambassador s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">chemes have had some success.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research cites prominent scientists, media personalities and teachers among the people who influence career choice, beyond members of the immediate family. The government funded scheme, science and engineering amb</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">assadors (SEAs) was established in 2000.  It increases the number of individuals in early </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">career </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">stages coming into contact with young</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sters</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">through</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> schools science clubs, to talk about their work.  SEAs were established in recognition of the fact that few </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">teachers have experience of working in industry, research or higher education.  Of those that do have relevant experience, by definition it will be limited and will date quickly, especially in fast moving areas such as IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.3.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Everywoman organisation is he</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">lping to address this through Leadership Academies; one day seminars for women in disciplines such as Technology, Engineering, Manufacturing, or Transport to boost their knowledge and be inspired by leading female figures as role models.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Recruitment Po</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">licies </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Where gendered names are removed from CVs in repeated trials and research, employers select males and females equally, based on the merits of skills</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research suggests that </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">using</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> female appropriate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recruitment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> advertising will benefit targets for employing women and conversely that where advertising is not positively constructed to be attractive to women, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">fewer women apply</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Where employers do not sufficiently train managers in techniques for advertising and int</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">erviewing women, gender imbalances proliferate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.4</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Lack of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nconscious </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ias training for hiring managers sets opinion in favour of the controlling group, which at this time in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">our</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> sector is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">overwhelmingly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">male. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">However, uptake and implementation </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of this type </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of education is sporadic</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and inconsistent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.5</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The IT industry requires many </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">business </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">skills, and recruit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> graduates with business skills and MBA qualifications can be benefi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cial</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> where there are declining numbers of graduates from pure ICT courses.  Anecdotally many individuals come to IT roles from different starting points</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  Th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e appeal of technology</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the opportunities available may not </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be apparent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">when </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">studying</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, but i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s greate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r when experienced in the workplace</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.6</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Dissemination of best practice on recruitment policies to make IT employers the companies of choice for women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> essential to ensure that the industry acquires the skills at both graduate and skilled practitioner levels</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  Guides are available from the UK Resource </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">entre for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">omen in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SET</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to encourage good </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recruitment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">practice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">; h</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">owever, incentive, uptake and implementation are sporadic, unmonitored, and inconsistent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">    </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.7</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Advertising a company’s WLB and Flexibility options </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">can make a difference and it is known that CISCO, IBM UK and others regularly do so</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.4.8</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Training in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nconscious </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">b</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ias has been undertaken </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">by all BCS</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Boards and Committees</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  This training is available from organisations such as WISE and is being rolled out in s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ome of the large technology companies.  IBM UK was one of the first to include this training for senior management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:13pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Career Paths, Retention and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Lack of O</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">pportunities for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">F</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">lexible </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">W</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">orking</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘Women are likely to be underrepresented within higher level (skilled/paid) ITEC occupations both compared to males and in terms of overall female </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">employment in ITEC.’  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Female </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">representation appears more focussed towards lower level ITEC occupations in the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UK than in other EU states</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><a name="_ftnref9"></a><a href="#_ftn9">[9]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This is also reflected by the 22% IT Gender Pay Gap, where fewer women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">earning in higher salary bands and th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">erefore a greater gap overall. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">orporate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">culture and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">practice may offer more challenging opportunities to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> males</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  There is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> assumption that women are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">less</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ambitio</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">u</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">than</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> men</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> a belief that where salaries are used as a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> success</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> indicator</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women are disadvantaged because of the gender pay gap in the IT sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">   </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A Gender Pay Audit was created durin</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">g the last administration and some private sector companies completed it, although the take-up was very limited.  One company which was willing to me</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ntion this practice was HSBC;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">who experience </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">blocked opportunities at senior levels, and perceive unfair selection criteria for executive and senior posts may act on their perceptions and leave the industry, which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">appears </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">anecdotally to be the case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Different modes of working are appropriate fo</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">r different life stages for both men and women.  This has been recognised by successive administrations and is not just related to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">STEM </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">roles.  We know that there are issues within the IT industry but believe that these will be beneficially impacted by cur</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rent programmes to enhance flexible working across all industries and we will</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> therefore not detail them here;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4.5.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The UKRC for SET held a very large repository of documentation and training on recruitment, mentoring and retention for women in STEM career</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s.  This might still be available from the WISE CIC. WISE also has a broad curriculum and series of materials for supporting organisations </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">wishing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to do more with women in STEM careers and supports females 'from classroom to boardroom'.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">4.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">6</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">ultures in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Education and Training</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We are aware that other respondents to this </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">inquiry</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">will cover this in detail and we believe that the issues are sufficiently known for us to not repeat them here. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><h2 style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; page-break-after:avoid; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">5</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">Recommendations for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; font-weight:bold">ction </span></h2><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">BCS aspires to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">deliver</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> best practice for diversity in the IT sector.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recommend the following </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">actions </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be undertaken to boost the number of women entering and staying in the STEM sector</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s, and in particular, within IT:</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.1 </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Quotas</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The argument against </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uotas has been fierce, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and resides around the desire for a meritocracy, and a desire that women succeed by right of their ability.  However, this pre-supposes that the current state of affairs represents a meritocracy</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, and that the industry will make progress through voluntary a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ctions.  Progress, however, continues to be slow and we therefore recommend that:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The debate should be reopened on setting q</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">uota</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s for women in STEM in academia and industry sectors.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This would include i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mplementation of monitoring and targets in all organi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">sations on the uptake of women into senior management and executive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and non-executive </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">positions</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.1.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">This debate should includ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> consultation on legislation regarding t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">he percentage of women on company boards</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, like </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">countries, compelling state owned and listed </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">private companies to appoint women to at least 30% of boardroom positions with severe penalties for those who do</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> not</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> conform;</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.2</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Use C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">urrent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">esources</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2.1</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Too often we </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">re-invent the wheel.  There are existing organisations, with good understa</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nding and relevant skill sets, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which can undertake key tasks associated with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">increasing the number of women </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in the STEM workforce.  These organisations could be </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">supported </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">with relatively minimal government funding to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">implement these recommendations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Organ</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">isations such as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> UKRC </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">(</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">which became WISE, and which was one of the founders of the Athena Swan initiative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">) and Everywoman</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> excellent </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">example</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">They</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> covers </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">all</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">of STEM</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and the business world as well as academia</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">, not just </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">engineering</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> discipline</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the current government </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">appears to favour</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Their missions are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">women and girls 'from the classroom to the boardroom' and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">to offer end to end solutions for aspiring female leaders and these </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">assets can </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">undoubtedly </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">support this renewed interes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t in driving gender diversity for the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">benefit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of UK PLC</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.2.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">No further research is required.  There is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> array of research from the UK and globally which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">articulates </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the issues and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">makes appropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">recommendations.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We need to get on and take the most pragm</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">atic approaches to fixing the problem.</span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.3</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Media and Imag</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">e</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Support </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">should </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">be given to tackle the media issues and could </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">include:</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">A campaign to feature articles and stories on women in IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ampaign</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to enhance the number of high profile women in IT in the media</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to provide role models</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">   </span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.3.3</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Work with TV production organisations on the inclus</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ion of positive female IT role </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">models in TV drama.  </span></p><p style="margin:12pt 0pt 3pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">5.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Role Models</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We make the following recommendations:</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4.1</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Implement a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">consistent programme to help teachers and other influential adults provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">realistic and appropriate </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">information and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">details of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">IT </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">role models </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">in order to take young people beyond being users of IT</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:3pt 0pt 3pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5.4.2</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Roll</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ing</span><span style=