.9pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">As a professional body, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">BCS</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> represents its members and the IT Profession as a whole on issues of importance, and liaises with other pr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">ofessional bodies, the government, industry and academics to initiate and inform debate on IT strategic issues. We also deliver a range of professional development tools for practitioners</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><a href="http://www.wisecampaign.org.uk/about-us/wise-resources/uk-statistics-2012"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:none">UK Statistics 2012, Women in Science, Technology, Engineering and Mathematics: from Classroom to Boardroom</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">according to e-skills’ Technology Insights 2012</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn4"></a><a href="#_ftnref4">[4]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> from ONS Labour Force Survey 2011 4 quarter average</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn5"></a><a href="#_ftnref5">[5]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> Management by Chuck W</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">illiams (7</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:6pt; vertical-align:super">th</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> edition 2012)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn6"></a><a href="#_ftnref6">[6]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> Work on Gender Schemas by Virginia Valian (Valian, V. (1998). ‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Why so slow? The advanceme